{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"188c082c-cceb-4fde-99a2-2cf50a6491a7","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nWith MTP, `dotnet test` no longer uses VSTest's `--filter` — it uses `--filter` with **MTP syntax**, which is different:\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe filter string itself actually looks the same, but MTP passes it through differently. The key issue is that **MTP requires `--` to separate its arguments**:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr use the MTP-native `--treenode-filter` for xUnit v3:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/IntegrationTests/**\"\n```\n\n### 2. Trait filtering with xUnit v3 + MTP\n\nFor trait-based filtering (`Category=Smoke`), xUnit v3 maps traits via `--treenode-filter` using a `/[Category=Smoke]/` syntax:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/MyApp.Tests/IntegrationTests[Category=Smoke]/**\"\n```\n\n### Recommended CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]/**\"\n```\n\nThis matches any test class containing `IntegrationTests` with the `Smoke` trait — equivalent to your original filter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16009503-97af-4a0d-9cbd-96f2a3b2cfd0","outputTokens":416,"requestId":"4C20:16C73:D72A1D:10BAE9D:6A012A5D"},"id":"28319838-e5f6-4b28-bcf5-79171cc1a8f8","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:01:27.233Z","parentId":"684ca64b-578c-465f-ab46-b20abf94e85b"}
